Heroku Postgres Upgrade Guide: Simplify Your Move to Version 17 (https://hello.heroku.com/e/36622/l-utm-campaign-2506-newsletter/m6ht2k/1309229782/h/eFnn5pPkC-hOxVtVrvfimoN_YJsW57lyxvX_uTh3Mbg)

Heroku has released an upgraded Postgres 17 experience with a major improvement: a new one-step, in-place upgrade process using the pg:upgrade CLI commands, eliminating the need to provision followers or juggle multiple commands. Most upgrades complete in about 5 to 10 minutes and automatically update follower databases, dramatically reducing downtime and complexity. With tools like pg:upgrade:dryrun, prepare, run, and wait, developers gain full control over staging, scheduling, and rollback during the upgrade process.
